snippet.textDisplay:
As much as I enjoyed "You", I have to admit that the actor playing the protagonist Joe -- his face never moves. I swear to you, the guy is the male version of gods-damned Kristen Stewart when it comes to showing emotion; the fella's face and eyes just remain locked in the same forced neutral expression for the entire series. He never shows happiness when he should, or panic, or anger, or fear, nor love, hate, irritation, contentedness, agitation -- anything.

He just looks like a dead fish with the same expression eternally plastered on his face, one in which the only emotion it's ever managed to evoke in me was amusement, and truly, even then it was only amusement at realising its uncanny resemblance to the face I make when I'm in the middle of straining lightly through a slightly difficult deuce, if that warns you any further about the face -- through thick and through thin -- in question itself ¯\_༼ ͡° ͜ʖ ͡° ༽_/¯
snippet.textOriginal:
